"```sql\nSELECT posts.Id AS PostId, badges.Name AS BadgeName\nFROM users\nJOIN posts ON users.Id = posts.OwnerUserId\nJOIN badges ON users.Id = badges.UserId\nWHERE users.DisplayName = 'Samuel'\n  AND YEAR(posts.CreationDate) = 2013\n  AND YEAR(badges.Date) = 2013;\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the post IDs and badge names for the user with the display name \"Samuel\" in the year 2013. It joins the `users`, `posts`, and `badges` tables based on the foreign key relationships and filters the results based on the specified conditions."